  code: 2B
  story: "As the moment came, Cinder hesitated and allowed doubt to silence him.
    His stepmother dismissed him, and the opportunity passed unnoticed. Life continued
    as before, but the memory of the ball lingered. \n\nDays later, Elara, guided
    by instinct rather than proof, sought him out. Found again among ashes, Cinder
    faced the choice he had avoided. This time, he chose to leave, not because he
    had been discovered, but because he recognized his own worth beyond fear. \n\nWithout
    the slipper or public recognition, his future changed through his own decision
    to step beyond the life imposed on him."
  defaultStory: {fileID: 0}
